org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.config

Class VeluxBridgeConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.config.VeluxBridgeConfiguration
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    VeluxBinding

    @NonNullByDefault
public class VeluxBridgeConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object
    The VeluxBridgeConfiguration is a wrapper for configuration settings needed to access the VeluxBridgeProvider device.

    It contains the factory default values as well.

    • protocol protocol type (one of http or https or slip),
    • ipAddress bridge IP address,
    • tcpPort bridge TCP port,
    • password bridge password,
    • timeoutMsecs communication timeout in milliseconds,
    • retries number of retries (with exponential backoff algorithm),
    • refreshMSecs refreshMSecs interval for retrieval of bridge information.
    • isBulkRetrievalEnabled flag to use bulk product
    • isSequentialEnforced flag to enforce sequential control on actuators.
    • isProtocolTraceEnabled flag to enable protocol logging (via loglevel INFO).

    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution
